#10011
Upper Southern Stands~
Rows upon rows of stone seating stretch far to the east, and they are stacked
upon each other like steps leading lower into the coliseum to your south.  
There is garbage strewn about everywhere, and puddles of questionable liquids
dirty your boots with each step.  At this height, the combat in the area is a
bit distant, but you have still got a great view.  The air is humming with the
cheering of the crowd.  The air is humming with the cheering of the crowd.  
At the very top of the stands, the seating levels off and leaves some standing
room for the poor spectators unable to find seats.  
~
