#10051
The Podium~
Decadently decorated with richly colored fabrics, gold leaf, and padded wooden
chairs, there is a distinct air of nobility in these balconies.  Prominently
poised over the arena grounds, the view from here is spectacular.  Large
curtains cover the stone walls here in an effort dampen the sounds of the
thundering crowd, but they have a very limited effect.  Large carved marble
columns support a roof that juts out over the balconies and provides superior
shade and comfort for the elite society of Kir Draxin.  It is clear that this
is a place of honor and the general public is not permitted entry.  The
balconies continue to the north.  To the south a pair of large, heavy curtains
covers the exit to the concourse.  
~
