#10055
The Concessions~
Vendor stalls are packed tightly along the western wall of this room.  
Various patrons wait in line for streetfood and beer.  The unmistakable smells
of fried meat contrast with the many baskets of bread, fruits, and sweets
lining the stall tables.  Several stalls have huge oaken barrels filled to be
brim with beer, with children scurrying back and forth to get drinks to
customers.  To the east the concourse is visible, and vendor stalls continue
onward to the north.  
~
