#10059
The Combatant Preparation Chambers~
This room is lined with simple wooden benches along the walls.  There is
equipment of varying, albeit relatively low, quality strewn about the room.  
There are a couple grizzled veterans quietly preparing for battle in one
corner of the room.  It is an unfortunate truth that this is the last place,
aside from the arena grounds themselves, that many a young man has seen.  
Through the door on the western wall, the beast pens across the hallway are
clearly visible.  
~
